const vh = window.innerHeight; const scrollFx = () => { const ds = window.scrollY; const offset = vh / 4; panels.forEach((panel) => { if (panel.parentElement.offsetTop < ds + offset) { panel.classList.add("panel__content--active"); } else { panel.classList.remove("panel__content--active"); } }); }; // Reveal the first panel by default panels[0]?.classList.add("panel__content--active"); // Attach the event listener window.addEventListener("scroll", scrollFx);
